comment:
Warner Bros will never get any money from me, ever again, unless they apologize and rehire Johnny Depp. I realize they won't, but I can do without their products. Firing Amber Heard won't placate me, at all. I'm opposed to canceling individuals; that should be left to the courts. I've never been a fan of Johnny Depp, nor of Amber Heard. I like his acting and think she's fairly pretty; beyond that, I've never had any opinion about either of them, until now. The reasons for my engagement are that...

...it's simply unfair, on an individual basis.
...it's sex discrimination.
...it punishes the victim.
...it's victim blaming.
...it's stupid beyond belief; I cannot support any entity displaying such stupidity.
...it's privatized "justice", which is about as accurate as tossing a coin, and invites disaster.
...it rewards the abuser, who threatened JD with exactly this type of scenario; WB is now complicit in the abuse.
*And most importantly:*
...it harms millions of other victims. Between 30% and 40% of domestic violence is female on male, and male victims have enough trouble being heard and believed, even without this.
